<div class="lb-section-row region-body"><div class="lb-region lb-region--left"><div class="block block-layout-builder block-inline-blockrelated-missions"><h2>More from UNICEF USA</h2><div class="views-element-container"><div class="view view-related-missions view-id-related_missions view-display-id-missions js-view-dom-id-e54e2419025692585d40938fe7d71ae2a99126f23c0b21b2a551268534571862"><div class="view-content"><div class="item-list"><ul><li><div class="views-field views-field-title"><span class="field-content"><a href="/what-unicef-does/where-unicef-works/africa/somalia" hreflang="en">UNICEF in Somalia</a></span></div></li><li><div class="views-field views-field-title"><span class="field-content"><a href="/what-unicef-does/where-unicef-works/asia/india" hreflang="en">UNICEF in India</a></span></div></li><li><div class="views-field views-field-title"><span class="field-content"><a href="/what-unicef-does/where-unicef-works/africa/libya" hreflang="en">UNICEF in Libya</a></span></div></li><li><div class="views-field views-field-title"><span class="field-content"><a href="/what-unicef-does/where-unicef-works/africa/mozambique" hreflang="en">UNICEF in Mozambique</a></span></div></li><li><div class="views-field views-field-title"><span class="field-content"><a href="/what-unicef-does/where-unicef-works/south-america/brazil" hreflang="en">UNICEF in Brazil</a></span></div></li><li><div class="views-field views-field-title"><span class="field-content"><a href="/what-unicef-does/where-unicef-works/asia/pakistan" hreflang="en">UNICEF in Pakistan</a></span></div></li><li><div class="views-field views-field-title"><span class="field-content"><a href="/what-unicef-does/childrens-health/parenting/heatwaves" hreflang="en">UNICEF: How to Keep Kids Safe and Healthy During a Heat Wave</a></span></div></li><li><div class="views-field views-field-title"><span class="field-content"><a href="/what-unicef-does/cash-transfers" hreflang="en">Humanitarian Cash Transfers</a></span></div></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="lb-region lb-region--right"><div class="block block-layout-builder block-inline-blockrecommended-stories-mini"><h2>Recommended Stories</h2><div class="teaser-column"><article class="node node--type-story node--view-mode-card"><div class="node__content"><a href="/stories/armenia-ukraine-unicef-maps-out-humanitarian-action-children-2024" ref="bookmark"><div class="field field--name-field-header-image field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden field__item"><figure class="media media--type-image media--view-mode--50-width"><img src="/sites/default/files/styles/50_percent/public/2023-12/UNI328446%20%281%29.jpg?itok=cloejxFm" width="458" height="305" alt="Seven schoolchildren, members of the indigenous community of Chicoy of Todos Santos Cuchumatnin, who live in the province of Huehuetenango, Guatemala, laugh and smile together on the floor of their classroom on the last day of school." loading="lazy" class="image-style-_0-percent" /></figure></div><h2><span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden">From Armenia to Ukraine: UNICEF Maps Out <strong>Humanitarian Action for Children in 2024</strong></span></h2><div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"><p>Some specific examples of how UNICEF plans to meet urgent and escalating needs of children in conflict and crisis hotspots around the world.</p></div></a></div></article><article class="node node--type-story node--promoted node--view-mode-card"><div class="node__content"><a href="/stories/back-school-after-volcanic-eruption-drc" ref="bookmark"><div class="field field--name-field-header-image field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden field__item"><figure class="media media--type-image media--view-mode--50-width"><img src="/sites/default/files/styles/50_percent/public/field-images/story-banner/2022/UN0637570.jpg.Banner6_0.jpg?itok=4eXTPhMV" width="458" height="344" alt="Students play during recess at Nziyi Primary School in Goma, Democratic Republic of the Congo." title="Students play during recess at Nziyi Primary School in Goma, Democratic Republic of the Congo." loading="lazy" class="image-style-_0-percent" /></figure></div><h2><span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden"><strong>Back to School</strong> After a Volcanic Eruption in DRC</span></h2><div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"><p>UNICEF is rebuilding schools and distributing learning supplies to help children resume their education in South Kivu Province. [VIDEO]</p></div></a></div></article><article class="node node--type-story node--view-mode-card"><div class="node__content"><a href="/stories/struggle-sustainability-sudan-transforming-lives-clean-water" ref="bookmark"><div class="field field--name-field-header-image field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden field__item"><figure class="media media--type-image media--view-mode--50-width"><img src="/sites/default/files/styles/50_percent/public/2024-02/UNI500244.jpg?itok=-iIu0Z14" width="458" height="305" alt="Children collect clean and safe water from a new water station in the small village of Gelhanty in Agig locality, Red Sea state, Sudan." loading="lazy" class="image-style-_0-percent" /></figure></div><h2><span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden">From Struggle to Sustainability in Sudan: <strong>Transforming Lives With Clean Water</strong></span></h2><div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"><p>How UNICEF helped children and women in Gelhanty, a small and remote village in Sudan's eastern Red Sea state, gain reliable access to safe water.</p></div></a></div></article></div></div></div></div> </section>
